  "read": "First HIP extension accumulator for actual-LI compressed dKV. It consumes materialized probs/grad_logits and active-group lists, so it is an accumulator-path smoke only. The body is scalar and serves as the binding/correctness rung before a CK-Tile/MFMA schedule. The optional tile-partial mode removes final global atomics by writing one partial row per seq-tile/group/D and then reducing those rows. The optional dense-group-tile mode keeps a dense local compressed-group table in LDS per seq/selected/D16 tile, then emits sparse global atomics only for touched groups. It is a runtime diagnostic for the coalesced-write budget, not the final CK-Tile/MFMA body.",
